description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a great oportunity for a Communications Officer to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A little bit about us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suffolk GP Federation is an innovative and rapidly growing organisation, with a workforce of around 700, which supports general practice in Suffolk and provides a portfolio of services to patients in Suffolk and the surrounding area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ve worked to establish a positive reputation within key media including East Anglian Daily Times, BBC Radio Suffolk and Pulse. We are looking to expand our Executive Support &amp; Communications Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A little bit about the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone to participate in the Federation’s communication and marketing function leading in the preparation and publishing of content for the Federation’s internal and external newsletters. You will also write press releases &amp; articles, and be the point of contact for all media enquiries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll need to be enthusiastic with a ‘can-do’ attitude and have the ability to juggle a variety of tasks with competing deadlines. We foster a team culture, and so your ability to work with a wide range of people is paramount.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We think this is an exciting role which you will have the opportunity to develop and shape&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to your application!&lt;/p&gt;
